give @s written_book{pages:['["",{"text":"Hostile Mob Spawning Mechanics","color":"dark_blue","clickEvent":{"action":"run_command","value":"/function give_a_book:table_of_contents"}},{"text":"\\nThere are 4 main conditions for hostile mobs to spawn.\\n1) For mobs to be able to spawn they need to be at least 24 blocks away from all players. I like to bridge out about 32-48 blocks away from the main island.","color":"reset"}]','{"text":"2) There needs to be room for the mob. If you don\\u2019t want Endermen, just keep the ceiling 2 blocks high, if you don\\u2019t want spiders, keep the room to a width of 1 block."}','["",{"text":"3) The spawning block needs to be solid. If you remember from the "},{"text":"Bridging section","color":"dark_blue","clickEvent":{"action":"run_command","value":"/function give_a_book:bridging"}},{"text":", mobs are not allowed to spawn on bottom-half slabs. Things like full cobblestone blocks or top-half slabs will work.","color":"reset"}]','{"text":"4) The top of the spawning block needs to be dark. You can either wait for night time or you can make a room that is closed off from the outside light. Light also doesn\\u2019t travel through half-slabs so you can make a little hole where you can stab at the mob\\u2019s feet safely."}','{"text":"Quick Warning: Because of these limitations it will become VERY easy for mobs to spawn. All of the mobs that would normally be spread out across a field and in random caves are now limited to the few exposed blocks on the islands."}','{"text":"If you leave your base without proper lighting, you WILL have mobs waiting for you when you get back.\\nExtra Note: Mob spawning starts at the bottom of the world, so if possible you should place a dark room/mob farm at the bottom of the world for faster spawns."}','{"text":"For Nether Mobs: There is no sun in the Nether, so blocks out in the void are considered dark.\\n\\nListed Below are the specific spawning requirements for each mob in alphabetical order:"}','[